        <p class="mt-5 text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight text-base-content">This tutorial guides you through the process of editing an existing Bonfire extension. We'll cover how to clone, enable, and contribute to an extension, ensuring you can test and implement your changes effectively.</p>
        <p class="mt-5 text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight text-base-content">Ideal for developers looking to modify and enhance Bonfire's functionalities.</p>
        <p class="mt-5 text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight text-base-content">By the end, you'll be adept at including and working with extensions in the Bonfire development environment.</p>
      
      
      <div class="p-4 border-info rounded bg-info/10">
        <h2 class="text-xs !m-0  uppercase text-info font-meidum tracking-widest">Prerequisites</h2>
        {# <p class="prose mt-2 !mb-0">Before diving into this tutorial, there are a few things you should have in place:<br/> #}
          <ul class="prose mt-0">
            <li>Basic understanding of Git.</li>
